        "heading": "Personal Infinitive",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The personal infinitive conjugates with person:"
          },
          {
            "type": "vocabulary",
            "items": [
              ["(eu) falar", "(para eu) falar"],
              ["(você) falar", "(para você) falar"],
              ["(ele/ela) falar", "(para ele/ela) falar"],
              ["(nós/a gente) falarmos/falar", "(para nós) falarmos"],
              ["(eles) falarem", "(para eles) falarem"]
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "heading": "'A Gente' Usage",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In Brazilian Portuguese, 'a gente' often replaces 'nós':"
          },
          {
            "type": "example",
            "source": "A gente foi ao cinema",
            "target": "We went to the movies",
            "note": "Third person singular verb"
          },
          {
            "type": "example",
            "source": "A gente se vê amanhã",
            "target": "We'll see each other tomorrow",
            "note": "Very common in spoken Brazilian Portuguese"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "heading": "Compound Tenses",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "vocabulary",
            "items": [
              ["Present Perfect", "Tenho falado (I have been speaking)"],
              ["Past Perfect", "Tinha falado (I had spoken)"],
              ["Future Perfect", "Vou ter falado / Terei falado"],
              ["Conditional Perfect", "Teria falado / Tinha falado (casual)"],
              ["Perfect Subjunctive", "Tenha falado"],
              ["Pluperfect Subjunctive", "Tivesse falado"]
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "heading": "Tips",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "tip",
            "text": "In Brazilian Portuguese, the imperfect often replaces the conditional: 'Eu ia fazer' instead of 'Eu faria'."
          },
